   <concept id="FAR_47_305_4" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">47.305-4</ph> F.o.b. destination solicitations.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2785e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2812e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            When preparing f.o.b destination solicitations, the contracting officer shall refer to <xref href="47.303.dita#FAR_47_303"
                        base="i1070167"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">47.303</xref> for the prescription of f.o.b. destination clauses relating to standard delivery terms.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2812e18">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            If f.o.b. destination only offers are desired, the solicitation shall state that offers submitted on a basis other than f.o.b. destination will be rejected as nonresponsive.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2812e23">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
						            When supplies will or may be purchased f.o.b. destination but inspection and acceptance will be at origin, the contracting officer shall insert in solicitations and contracts the clause at <xref href="52.247-48.dita#FAR_52_247_48"
                        base="i1046245"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.247-48</xref>, F.o.b. Destination-Evidence of Shipment.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
